definitions.definition: A geographic area and former division of Lincolnshire , England .
An Anglo-Saxon kingdom of England , absorbed into Northumbria in the 7th century.
A village and civil parish in Babergh district, Suffolk , England ( OS grid ref TL9845 ) .
A habitational surname from Old English .
A unisex given name transferred from the surname .
